FBIS4-8850 "dreeu075_i_94010" FBIS-EEU-94-075 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Serbs Begin Fresh Attack LD1904072694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0600 GMT 17 Apr 94 LD1904072694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] According to the latest report from Gorazde, following last night's relative lull, this morning at about 0400 Karadzic's Serbs launched fresh attacks on this town. Here is a report from Gorazde. [Correspondent Fahrudin Brkic] [passage indistinct] in the southeast part did not stop for a single moment. There was no respite either in an unprecedented exodus of people from their burning villages. [placenames indistinct] villages were put to the torch by the chetniks yesterday. The aggressor's infantry attacks were accompanied by artillery that pounded the entire town and its outlying suburbs until 0200 this morning. Following a brief lull, these operations resumed at about 0400. On the 20th day of the offensive against Gorazde [word indistinct] of this town has reached its culmination. Fahrudin Brkic reporting for Bosnia-Herzegovina Radio.
